 leftover cold gas from the precursor star forming galaxy mainly\nremoved by the long-lasting Ia SN feedback. The two different trends for\ngas-rich and -poor galaxies may be the results of the initial fast decreasing\nSN rate and the later fast decreasing mass-loading to hot gas, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 May 2011 21:09:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
