cular cloud and later homogenized in the\nprotoplanetary disk. The apparent lack of correlation between Al-26 abundance\nand O-isotope compositions of corundum grains put important constraints on the\nstellar source of Al-26 in the solar system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 May 2011 06:11:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
